annotationA: Probable methylmalonate-semialdehyde dehydrogenase [acylating], mitochondrial; Plays a role in valine and pyrimidine metabolism. Binds fatty acyl-CoA (By similarity); Belongs to the aldehyde dehydrogenase family
annotationB: GH13256p; acetyl-CoA C-acyltransferase activity; long-chain-3-hydroxyacyl-CoA dehydrogenase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: determination of adult lifespan; fatty acid beta-oxidation; Belongs to the thiolase family
